  68. ‌let public_method_label s : tag =
  69.   let accu = ref 0 in
  70.   for i = 0 to String.length s - 1 do
  71.     accu := 223 * !accu + Char.code s.[i]
  72.   done;
  73.   (* reduce to 31 bits *)
  74.   accu := !accu land (1 lsl 31 - 1);
  75.   (* make it signed for 64 bits architectures *)
  76.   let tag = if !accu > 0x3FFFFFFF then !accu - (1 lsl 31) else !accu in
  77.   (* Printf.eprintf "%s = %d\n" s tag; flush stderr; *)
  78.   Obj.magic tag

  143. ‌let resize array new_size =

  194. ‌let narrow table vars virt_meths concr_meths =
  195.   let vars = to_list vars
  196.   and virt_meths = to_list virt_meths
  197.   and concr_meths = to_list concr_meths in
  198.   let virt_meth_labs = List.map (get_method_label table) virt_meths in
  199.   let concr_meth_labs = List.map (get_method_label table) concr_meths in
  200.   table.previous_states <-
  201.      (table.methods_by_name, table.methods_by_label, table.hidden_meths,
  202.       table.vars, virt_meth_labs, vars)
  203.      :: table.previous_states;
  204.   table.vars <-
  205.     Vars.fold
  206.       (fun lab info tvars ->
  207.         if List.mem lab vars then Vars.add lab info tvars else tvars)
  208.       table.vars Vars.empty;
  209.   let by_name = ref Meths.empty in
  210.   let by_label = ref Labs.empty in
  211.   List.iter2
  212.     (fun met label ->
  213.        by_name := Meths.add met label !by_name;
  214.        by_label :=
  215.           Labs.add label
  216.             (try Labs.find label table.methods_by_label with Not_found -> true)
  217.             !by_label)
  218.     concr_meths concr_meth_labs;
  219.   List.iter2
  220.     (fun met label ->
  221.        by_name := Meths.add met label !by_name;
  222.        by_label := Labs.add label false !by_label)
  223.     virt_meths virt_meth_labs;
  224.   table.methods_by_name <- !by_name;
  225.   table.methods_by_label <- !by_label;
  226.   table.hidden_meths <-
  227.      List.fold_right
  228.        (fun ((lab, _) as met) hm ->
  229.           if List.mem lab virt_meth_labs then hm else met::hm)
  230.        table.hidden_meths
  231.        []

  233. ‌let widen table =
  234.   let (by_name, by_label, saved_hidden_meths, saved_vars, virt_meths, vars) =
  235.     List.hd table.previous_states
  236.   in
  237.   table.previous_states <- List.tl table.previous_states;
  238.   table.vars <-
  239.      List.fold_left
  240.        (fun s v -> Vars.add v (Vars.find v table.vars) s)
  241.        saved_vars vars;
  242.   table.methods_by_name <- by_name;
  243.   table.methods_by_label <- by_label;
  244.   table.hidden_meths <-
  245.      List.fold_right
  246.        (fun ((lab, _) as met) hm ->
  247.           if List.mem lab virt_meths then hm else met::hm)
  248.        table.hidden_meths
  249.        saved_hidden_meths

  311. let init_class table =
  312.   inst_var_count := !inst_var_count + table.size - 1;

  316. let inherits cla vals virt_meths concr_meths (_, super, _, env) top =
  317.   narrow cla vals virt_meths concr_meths;
  318.   let init =
  319.     if top then super cla env else Obj.repr (super cla) in
  320.   widen cla;
  321.   Array.concat
  322.     [[| Obj.repr init |];
  323.      Obj.magic (Array.map (get_variable cla) (to_array vals) : int array);
  324.      Array.map
  325.        (fun nm -> Obj.repr (get_method cla (get_method_label cla nm) : closure))
  326.        (to_array concr_meths) ]

  422. ‌let build_path n keys tables =
  423.   let res = Cons {key = Obj.magic 0; data = Empty; next = Empty} in
  424.   let r = ref res in
  425.   for i = 0 to n do
  426.     r := Cons {key = keys.(i); data = !r; next = Empty}
  427.   done;

  429.   res

  431. ‌let rec lookup_keys i keys tables =
  432.   if i < 0 then tables else
  433.   let key = keys.(i) in
  434.   let rec lookup_key (tables:tables) =
  435.     if get_key tables == key then
  436.       match get_data tables with
  437.       | Empty -> assert false
  438.       | Cons _ as tables_data ->
  439.           lookup_keys (i-1) keys tables_data
  440.     else
  441.       match get_next tables with
  442.       | Cons _ as next -> lookup_key next
  443.       | Empty ->
  444.           let next : tables = Cons {key; data = Empty; next = Empty} in
  445.           set_next tables next;
  446.           build_path (i-1) keys next
  447.   in
  448.   lookup_key tables

  450. ‌let lookup_tables root keys =

  510.     then n else new_method table
  511.   in
  512.   table.methods.(n) <- Obj.magic 0;
  513.   n

  515. ‌type impl =
  516.     GetConst
  517.   | GetVar
  518.   | GetEnv
  519.   | GetMeth
  520.   | SetVar
  521.   | AppConst
  522.   | AppVar
  523.   | AppEnv
  524.   | AppMeth
  525.   | AppConstConst
  526.   | AppConstVar
  527.   | AppConstEnv
  528.   | AppConstMeth
  529.   | AppVarConst
  530.   | AppEnvConst
  531.   | AppMethConst
  532.   | MethAppConst
  533.   | MethAppVar
  534.   | MethAppEnv
  535.   | MethAppMeth
  536.   | SendConst
  537.   | SendVar
  538.   | SendEnv
  539.   | SendMeth
  540.   | Closure of closure

  542. ‌let method_impl table i arr =
  543.   let next () = incr i; Obj.magic arr.(!i) in
  544.   match next() with
  545.     GetConst -> let x : t = next() in get_const x
  546.   | GetVar   -> let n = next() in get_var n
  547.   | GetEnv   -> let e = next() in let n = next() in get_env e n
  548.   | GetMeth  -> let n = next() in get_meth n
  549.   | SetVar   -> let n = next() in set_var n
  550.   | AppConst -> let f = next() in let x = next() in app_const f x
  551.   | AppVar   -> let f = next() in let n = next () in app_var f n
  552.   | AppEnv   ->
  553.       let f = next() in  let e = next() in let n = next() in
  554.       app_env f e n
  555.   | AppMeth  -> let f = next() in let n = next () in app_meth f n
  556.   | AppConstConst ->
  557.       let f = next() in let x = next() in let y = next() in
  558.       app_const_const f x y
  559.   | AppConstVar ->
  560.       let f = next() in let x = next() in let n = next() in
  561.       app_const_var f x n
  562.   | AppConstEnv ->
  563.       let f = next() in let x = next() in let e = next () in let n = next() in
  564.       app_const_env f x e n
  565.   | AppConstMeth ->
  566.       let f = next() in let x = next() in let n = next() in
  567.       app_const_meth f x n
  568.   | AppVarConst ->
  569.       let f = next() in let n = next() in let x = next() in
  570.       app_var_const f n x
  571.   | AppEnvConst ->
  572.       let f = next() in let e = next () in let n = next() in let x = next() in
  573.       app_env_const f e n x
  574.   | AppMethConst ->
  575.       let f = next() in let n = next() in let x = next() in
  576.       app_meth_const f n x
  577.   | MethAppConst ->
  578.       let n = next() in let x = next() in meth_app_const n x
  579.   | MethAppVar ->
  580.       let n = next() in let m = next() in meth_app_var n m
  581.   | MethAppEnv ->
  582.       let n = next() in let e = next() in let m = next() in
  583.       meth_app_env n e m
  584.   | MethAppMeth ->
  585.       let n = next() in let m = next() in meth_app_meth n m
  586.   | SendConst ->
  587.       let m = next() in let x = next() in send_const m x (new_cache table)
  588.   | SendVar ->
  589.       let m = next() in let n = next () in send_var m n (new_cache table)
  590.   | SendEnv ->
  591.       let m = next() in let e = next() in let n = next() in
  592.       send_env m e n (new_cache table)
  593.   | SendMeth ->
  594.       let m = next() in let n = next () in send_meth m n (new_cache table)
  595.   | Closure _ as clo -> Obj.magic clo

  597. ‌let set_methods table methods =
  598.   let len = Array.length methods in let i = ref 0 in
  599.   while !i < len do
  600.     let label = methods.(!i) in let clo = method_impl table i methods in
  601.     set_method table label clo;
  602.     incr i
  603.   done

  605. (**** Statistics ****)

  607. ‌type stats =
  608.   { classes: int; methods: int; inst_vars: int; }

  610. ‌let stats () =
  611.   { classes = !table_count;
  612.     methods = !method_count; inst_vars = !inst_var_count; }
